; Sturm's house

VARIABLE TRAPDEACT
VARIABLE STURMTALON
VARIABLE STURMSEARCH

NUMBER 759
DARKNESS
INDOOR_FLOOR
NAME New Everhome
*DESCRIPTION_START
As soon as you enter this home you notice the perfect blending of both nature
and man. Many of the items within the room represent not one race but many. A
magnificent plush azure rug covers the entire floor and is so deep that you
barely see the tops of your feet. Directly in front of you and taking up much
of the rear of the house is a massive statue of a dragon. Its eyes seem to
stare directly at you no matter where you stand and they gleam with
intelligence. Set in front of the statue is a large mirmach desk that
has been polished to a high gloss. On the walls are portraits of three
individuals who blend perfectly with this home. A comfortable couch sits
before a huge fireplace set into the eastern wall. A stout door goes out.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT BELOW 758
ITEM 0 944 ADJ1=949 ADJ2=577 VAL2=758
ITEM 1 362 ADJ1=239 ADJ2=19
ITEM 2 346
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
You gaze upon one of the most beautiful creatures you have ever imagined.
His scales are of the purest platinum and they cover a frame of strength
and power. His wings, if opened, would be as long as three houses put
together and his talons are razor sharp and look capable of cutting
through stone and metal. Yet for some reason the fierce likeness inspires
feelings of friendship, and understanding rather than fear. One could even
fancy a look of wisdom and kindness upon the dragon's face. The longer you
look at this statue, the more you think you should remember something more.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 3 201 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=196
PUT 3 1312 ADJ1=32
ITEM 4 1308
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
This is a portrait of Drizzt Do'Urden, a highlander of great strength and
high determination. He is wearing a suit of battle worn plate mail and upon
his head is a helm shaped into the figure of a dragon with upswept wings.
Upon his left hand is a glittering ruby ring of the Crimson Band. He stands
in the forefront of a battle covered with blood and gore wielding a gleaming
titanium staff which emits a eerie black radius. About him lie many dead and
dying trolls from many tribes. His lavender eyes blaze with an inner fire
and his face is a mask of rage and retribution as he literally drives his
staff completely through the breast and out the back of one of the mightiest
trolls you have ever seen, obviously the chief and king of these combined
tribes. This is the fulfillment of a vow he made to himself when, many
years before, he was forced to flee to protect a dying aelfen woman's
baby. In the background are two other figures and what is left of
village where many races once dwelt.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 5 1308
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
Upon this portrait is a young aelfen who is usually known for his kindness
and ready smile, but on this occasion his face is twisted into a fearsome
visage. He is Sturm Brightblade, a mage of known power and varied skill.
He wears a suit of eldritch leather armor and a pointed hat with mystic
designs, but it is the arcane bands of power about him that offer his
greatest protection. He is situated between Drizzt, who he considers his
older brother, and a ferocious gargoyle as they guard either side of him
so he may not be disturbed during his magical workings. Strewn about are
the fruits of his labor. Troll shamen clutching ghastly burns from the
unending flow of intensely cold spheres that fly from his fingers. Scores
of troll warriors hideously smashed and buried by a rain of huge meteors.
And from every direction woodland creatures come to his call to fall upon
the vast hordes of trolls. He is standing at the entry of a ruined house.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 6 1308
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 6
This is a portrait of Trapspringer Burrfoot, a strange and humorous mechanoid
with bizarre taste in clothing. He appears in this scene wearing a turban with
a ruby set into it's center, some glittering silver mail which reminds you of
the stars on a moonless night and some fuzzy pink bunny slippers with long
ears. He sits in the middle of Fayd's bazaar center with a gleeful expression
on his face as the chest he was working on explodes, thus living up to his
name. Other citizens wait in line to be his next customers as his skill
with opening locks is well know. He is a newcomer to Fayd, having been
found, abandoned in a old ruin, by his new friends Drizzt and Sturm, but
he is fast making a name for himself.
*DESCRIPTION_END
