NUMBER 440
NAME The Lair
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
The room you have entered is huge, though there are many things to see
there is still plenty of space for comfortable living. One area is
devoted to a place of study. Many books and scrolls are neatly kept
upon shelves and a desk for reading sit in the center of this area.
Another area has been set up for some type of mechanical
experimentation. The experiments range from devious traps for chests
and doors to partially completed robots for combat practice. Yet
another area is devoted to the arts of combat. Many mangled and
smashed robots lie about. They range from human shapes to ferocious
animals. Set aside from all of this is what could only be a sleeping
area with three beds that are partitioned from one another to offer
privacy.
*DESCRIPTION_END

